hopobject.body: Excellent work, Nice Design dallah pharma riyadh address The second tile, similar to one found at Glastonbury Abbey, is a depiction of a helmeted King Richard I (1189-1199) on horseback, charging his enemy. The tile "would originally have had an opposing tile showing Saladin, Sultan of Egypt, also in a symbolic combat pose," according to Wessex Archaeology. "These two great adversaries were involved in the Third Crusade (1189â1192) and are often depicted together on this type of floor tile."
